SIMPLE: situated
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Situated
<hw>Sit"u*a`ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL. <ets>situatus</ets>, from
<ets>situare</ets> to place, fr. L. <ets>situs</ets> situation, site.
See <er>Site</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having a site, situation, or
location; being in a relative position; permanently fixed; placed;
located; <as>as, a town <ex>situated</ex>, or <ex>situate</ex>, on a
hill or on the seashore</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Placed; residing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Pleasure <qex>situate</qex> in hill and dale.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Situate</xex> is now less used than
<xex>situated</xex>, but both are well authorized.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Situate</ent>⟦br⟧
